1. g3 b6 2. Bg2 Nc6 3. d3 Bb7 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. O-O d5 6. Nc3 e5 7. Nd2?! { this passive move allows Black to seize the initiative } 7... d4! 8. Nce4 Be7?! (8... Nxe4! 9. Nxe4 Qd7 $17 { followed by f5 could give Black a significant
advantage }) 9. Nxf6+ Bxf6 10. e4 dxe3? (10... Qe7 11. f4 O-O-O { would give
Black a comfortable position }) 11. fxe3 Bg5? { this natural move doesn't work
due to following tactics } 12. Ne4 Bh6 13. Qh5 O-O 14. Bd2? (14. Nf6+! gxf6 15. Qxh6 { could win the game for White }) 14... Qd7? { it fails tactically } (14... f6 { the game goes on }) 15. Nf6+ { it's good enough for White to win } (15. Qxh6! gxh6 16. Nf6+ { was a more
straightforward way to win } 16... Kg7 17. Nxd7 { winning a piece }) 15... gxf6 16. Qxh6 f5 17. Rxf5!? { not the best but a very interesting option indeed } (17. Qg5+ Kh8 18. Qf6+ Kg8 19. Rxf5 { was a simpler way for White to win }) 17... Qxf5 18. Be4 Ne7 19. Bxf5 Nxf5 20. Qg5+ Ng7 21. e4 f6 22. Qg4 f5 23. exf5 Rxf5 24. Bh6 Rf7 25. Bxg7 Rxg7 26. Qe6+ Kh8 27. Rf1 Rag8 28. Rf7 Rxf7 29. Qxf7 e4 30. dxe4 Bxe4 31. Qf6+ Rg7 32. Qd8+ Rg8 33. Qd4+ Rg7 34. Qxe4 h6 35. Qe5 Kh7 36. Qxg7+ Kxg7 37. Kf2 Kf6 38. Kf3 a5 39. h3 Kf5 40. g4+ Kg5 41. Kg3 a4 42. h4+ Kg6 43. Kf4 Kf6 44. b3 axb3 45. axb3 b5 46. g5+ hxg5+ 47. hxg5+ Kg6 48. b4 c6 49. c3 Kh5 50. Ke5 Kg4 51. Kd6 c5 52. Kxc5 Kxg5 53. Kxb5 Kf5 54. c4 Ke4 55. Kb6 Kd3 56. c5 Kc3 57. c6 Kb3 58. c7 { White wins } 1-0


