and the two passed pawns on the kingside are powerful. } 26. Rf1 f3 27. a4 { Diagram # White don't have any good moves here... } 27... Rc4! 28. Bxc4 (28. Ba5 Nxa4+ 29. Bxa4 Rxa4 $19 30. Bc7 Rb4+ 31. Kc1 Bxc3) 28... Nxc4+ 29. Kc1 (29. Kb3 Nd2+) (29. Kb1 Nd2+) (29. Ka2 a5 30. Bc5 Bxc3 31. Kb3 Nd2+! 32. Kxc3 Nxf1) 29... Bh6+ 30. Kd1 Ne3+ 31. Ke1 Nxc2+! { It's better to capture a piece and not the exchange... :-) } 32. Kf2 Nxb4 33. Rd1 f5 $19 34. Rd6 Bf8 35. Rd8 (35. Rxg6+ Kf7 36. Rg5 Ke6 37. Nd1 Bc5+ 38. Kf1 Ke5 $19 { Black's kingside pawns are powerful. }) 35... Kf7 36. Kg3 Bc5 37. Nd1 Ke6 38. Rd2 Nd5 39. a5 Nf6 40. Rc2 Nh5+ 41. Kh2 g3+ { 0-1 Black wins. } (41... Kh1 42. Kd5 a6 43. Nf4 Ra2 44. g2+ Rxg2 45. fxg2+ Kh2 46. g1=Q#) 0-1


