1. e4 d6 2. d4 e6 3. Bd3 b6 4. Ne2 Bb7 5. O-O g6 6. Be3 Bg7 7. Nd2 Nd7 8. f4 Nh6 (8... Ne7) 9. Nf3 f5 10. e5 Qe7 11. Qd2 Nf7 (11... Ng4 { was stronger } { [%cal Gg4e3] }) 12. Rad1 O-O-O 13. a4 dxe5 14. fxe5 h6 15. a5 b5? { it's too risky } (15... g5) 16. a6 Ba8 (16... Bxa6? 17. Ra1 { [%cal Ga1a7] }) 17. Bxb5 Ndxe5 { [%cal Gd8d2] } 18. Nxe5 Nxe5 19. Qc3 Ng4 20. Bf4 e5 21. dxe5 Nxe5 22. Nd4 c5 23. Rfe1 Rxd4 24. Rxd4 Nf3+ 25. gxf3 (25. Kf1! Nxe1 26. Rd7 { was stronger for White but it's really hard to find such moves in a real game }) 25... Bxd4+ 26. Kg2 Qh4 27. Bg3 Qg4? { Black keeps trying to checkmate White
but it back fires... } (27... Bxc3! 28. Bxh4 Bxe1 29. Bxe1 { leads to a
winning endgame for Black due to his material advantage }) 28. Qb3 { [%cal Gb3e6] } 28... f4 29. Bc4 { [%cal Gc4e6] } 29... Qg5 (29... Qxf3+ 30. Qxf3 Bxf3+ 31. Kxf3 fxg3 32. Kxg3) 30. Bg8 { Decisive and quite unexpected. } (30. Re7!! { was
even better } 30... Qxe7 31. Be6+ Kc7 32. Bxf4+ Kd8 33. Qb8#) 30... Be3 31. Rxe3 fxe3 32. Qb8+ Kd7 33. Qxa7+ Ke8 34. Qxa8+ Ke7 35. Qb7+ Ke8 36. a7 { 1-0 White wins. } { [%cal Ga7a8] } 1-0


