1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. f3 c6?! { 1. Your opening moves should either develop a
piece or influence the center. } 4. c4 g6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Be3 O-O 7. Nge2 (7. Bd3) 7... Nbd7 8. Qd2 a6 9. a4 { 2. Watch over your opponent's ideas and prevent
them. } 9... c5 (9... e5) 10. d5 (10. dxc5 Nxc5) 10... Nb6 (10... Ne5 { 3. Move
towards the center }) 11. Ng3 e6 12. a5 Nbd7 (12... exd5 13. axb6 d4) 13. dxe6 Ne5 (13... fxe6 14. Qxd6) 14. exf7+ Rxf7 15. Be2 (15. Bxc5 Be6 16. Bd4) 15... Be6 16. Nd5 { It's preferable to move a piece (not a pawn) when there's a
simingly equal choice. } 16... Nxd5 17. cxd5 { We've seen this idea already - move
towards the center. } 17... Bd7 18. O-O b5 19. axb6 Qxb6 20. Ra5 { 4. When unsure what
to do - activate your least active piece. } 20... Bc8 21. Rfa1 Rc7 22. h3 { 5. Don't
rush to attack, improve your position first. } 22... Qb3 23. R1a3 Qb6 24. f4 Nf7 25. b3 Re7 26. Bc4 (26. e5 dxe5 27. Bxc5) 26... Nd8 27. e5 Nb7 28. Rxa6 Rxa6 29. Rxa6 Qc7 30. Ne4 Kh8 (30... dxe5 31. d6+) 31. exd6 Nxd6 32. Rc6 (32. Rxd6 Rxe4) 32... Nxe4 33. Rxc7 Rxc7 (33... Nxd2) 34. Qa5 Rd7 35. Qa8 Rd8 36. Qc6 Bf6 37. Bd3 Bd7 38. Qb6 Bd4 39. Qxd8+ { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


